<paragraph blockId="9.[164,779,1636,1903]" lastBlockId="9.[826,1441,805,857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[164,300,1637,1658]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Description:</emphasis>
Male. Head: frons almost black. Face almost brown. Thorax: black with silver-grey pollinose pattern. Scutellum orange-yellow medially, black along margin, yellow at tip. Legs: hind tibia with three black rings, lacking any long setae (
<figureCitation box="[657,724,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="5.[164,254,1159,1178]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–6. Hindlegs of male. For details of the parts denoted by letters a–e see the descriptions of individual species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687815/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). All fifth tarsomeres black, the rest grey yellow. Male terminalia: epandrium elongated ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[685,767,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figures 22, 23" captionStartId="9.[164,254,698,717]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetId="figure-462@9.[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 22, 23. Phortica longicauda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 22, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 23, hypan- drium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687829/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Cercus with three long setae (
<figureCitation box="[508,590,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figures 22, 23" captionStartId="9.[164,254,698,717]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetId="figure-462@9.[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 22, 23. Phortica longicauda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 22, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 23, hypan- drium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687829/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with one prensiseta apically (
<figureCitation box="[449,531,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figures 22, 23" captionStartId="9.[164,254,698,717]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetId="figure-462@9.[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 22, 23. Phortica longicauda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 22, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 23, hypan- drium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687829/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Paramere submedially with two small processes and two sensilla; basal process lacking fine sawteeth (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1267,835,857]" captionStart="Figures 22, 23" captionStartId="9.[164,254,698,717]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetId="figure-462@9.[387,1219,195,668]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 22, 23. Phortica longicauda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 22, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 23, hypan- drium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687829/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="368">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
